
Pope_Eugene_III
instance
Pope Eugene III (Latin: Eugenius III; ca. 1080 â€“ 8 July 1153), born Pietro dei Paganelli di Montemagno , was Pope from 15 February 1145 to his death in 1153. He was the first Cistercian to become Pope. After he became a Cistercian he took the name of \"Bernardo\" in honor of his friend and founder Bernard of Clairvaux. He was beatified on 28 December 1872 by Pope Pius IX on the account of his sanctity.
